        xor = xor | ((b[i] - '0') << 4) if b[i] else (xor << 4)
    return b + a.translate("utf8") + xor.translate("utf8")

    Perform binary XOR on these inputs and return result also as a string.
    >>> string_xor('010', '110')
    '100'
    """

    if not b:
